Copy AMI:
-----------------------------------
Create a copy of an Amazon Machine Image in a Region

When you want to create a copy of your AMI  follow these steps:

Step 1: Enter the AMI copy name
Step 2: Enter the AMI copy description 
Step 3: Destination Region 
Step 4: Select the optoin Copy-tag if you want to copy the tags
Step 5: Enabel time based copy [ If you want to  want to complete the copie of the 
                                 AMI withing a specific time ,this time applies to 
                                 individual volume separately ]
Step 6: Choose whether  to Encrypt the EBS snapshots of AMI copy 
Step 7: If you want to add the tags click on add the new tag [ You can also choose wheather
                                                               to applie the tags individually 
                                                                or together for the snapshot and image ]
Step 8: Create

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Edit AMI permission 
-------------------------
By editing the permission of an AMI ,you can share it with the AWS accounts 
,organizations or OUs that you specify 

By following these steps you can edit the permission:

Step 1: AMI availability  
        \_Public - Share the AMI publically with all the AWS users 
        \_Private - Share the AMI with specific accounts ,organizations or OU's

Step 2:  Associated snapshot settings
       \_Manage permissions for all snapshots that are associated with 
         the selected AMI .You can manage individual snapshot sharing 
         permission on the snapshot page 

         Permission to create volume from snapshots
        \_applies only when sharing with specific AWS accounts .Allows shared
          accounts to create EBS volumes from the  AMI's snapshot ,in additionn to 
          launching the instance

Step 3: Shared accounts
        \_ Here you can add the accounts or remove the accounts by there accout ID
Step 4: Shared organization: 
        \_Here you can add a organization or OU ARN   or remove by there ARN 
____________________________________________________________________________________________________
Manage Tags
-----------------------
A Tag is a custom label that you assign to an AWS resources .You can use tags to help organize and Identify your Images

Step 1: Click on Add tag to add the tag
         \_ where you should specify  Key and Value 
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Deregister AMI
-------------------------
This means remove the  AMI from your account 
Note: Yu should manually delete this associated snapshots afterward 

After you deregister  an AMI ,you can't use it to launch new instances
____________________________________________________________________________________________
Manage AMI deregistration protection 
-------------------------------------------
You can protect an AMI from being deregistered by enabling deregistration protection 
You can also include a 24-hour cooldown period during wich deregistration protection 
remain enforced when you disable deregistration protection 

Deregistration protection:
\_Disable
\_Enabel with a 24-hour cooldown period
\_Enabel without cooldown 
