Manage AMI Deprecation 
-------------------------------
You can deprecate an AMI to indicate that it is out of data and should not be used .
You can also specify a future  deprecation  data for an AMI ,indication when the AMI will be out of date

Step 1: Enabel the Deprecate (tion) of the AMI
Step 2: Specify the Deprecation Date and Time 
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Register Instance store-backed AMI
------------------------------------------
Most modern AMI's are:
*EBS backed ->  Stored as EBS snapshosts
But older AMI's can be : 
* Instance-store-backed -> stored as files in Amazon S3 ,not EBS 

Instance-store-backed  AMI's boot from the local NVMe/SATA disks   not from EBS volumes 
These AMI's are rare and old and mostly used in on-prem migration ro legacy system 

Summary : 
*Register instances store-backed AMI
 Allows you to manually register an AMI that boots from  instances store 
 not EBS
*Require an image manifest
 This files in S3 describing how the AMI is built
*Used for old/legacy systems
 Not for new workloads
______________________________________________________________________________________________________
Configure the fast launch 
-------------------------------
Windows instances normally take longer to boot than Linux because windows perform 
*Disk setup
*Driver initialization 
*Sysprep customization 
*OS optimization 

Fast Launch prepares the AMI in advance so that : 
*Boot time becomes faster 
*Instance start up in second instead of minutes 

Not needed for the:
* Linux AMI'S
* Low Scale systems 
__________________________________________________________________________________________
Disable AMI
-----------------------------------
After you disable the AMI,it is made private and its state is changed to disabeled .
YOu can't launch a new Ec2 instance from a disabled AMI 

Archive the Associated snapshots:
To reduce your snapshots  storage costs ,you can archive the snapshots after 
You disable your AMI .YOu can archive snapshots the snapshot screen  
If you want you can re-enble your AMI  .You'll need to move the snapshots
associated with the AMI back from the archive tier to the standard snapshot tier
